events.name: I/O Extended Pokhara
events.description:
Google I/O Extended
Register Here

I/O Extended events include a variety of options for developers—from live streaming sessions to local demos, to hackathons, code-labs, design sprint and more. These events are hosted in your neighborhood by local developer communities.

As a part of I/O Extended series, GDG Kathmandu is organizing "Design Sprint" in WRC, Pokhara with following agendas:

• Prototyping Techniques

• Identification of Solutions Based On Problem Statement

• Ideation and brainstorming

• Prototype your idea

• How to pitch your idea effectively

events.name: I/O Extended Kathmandu
events.description:
A design sprint is a five-phase framework that helps answer critical business questions through rapid prototyping and user testing. The process helps spark innovation, encourage user-centered thinking, align your team under a shared vision, and get you to product launch faster.

As a part of I/O Extended series, GDG Kathmandu is organizing "Design Sprint Kathmandu" with following agendas:

• Prototyping Techniques

• Identification of Solutions Based On Problem Statement

• Ideation and brainstorming

• Prototype your idea

• How to pitch your idea effectively

events.description:
International Women's Day Celebration is annual celebration event for females in technology, organized by Women TechMakers. This year, IWD 2018 will be celebrated in April 7, 2018, Saturday.
Location: Work Around, Kalopul, Kathmandu

events.name: Google IO Extended Kathmandu 2018
events.description:
Google I/O is a developer festival that was held May 8-10 at the Shoreline Amphitheatre in Mountain View, CA. I/O brings together developers from around the globe annually for talks, hands-on learning with Google experts, and the first look at Google’s latest developer products.
I/O Extended events are hosted by local developers all around the world as local developers festival. As a part of this global series, GDG Kathmandu is organizing this event on:
Date: 14th July
Time: 10 am to 5 pm
Venue: Bougainvilla Events, Tripureshwor

Register for the event here: https://goo.gl/forms/h4VVeUgH2COF7EHG2

Google IO Extended Kathmandu 2018 is a two-track event with workshop, speaker series, code labs and networking opportunities.

The agenda :
Track 1 :
1.Speaker series
2.AI workshop (4 hours)- registration and confirmation required

Track 2:
1.Codelabs (Android, AI/ML, IOT, Firebase)
2. Community lounge

For more details :
Write to [masked] or call[masked]
If you wish to join Codelabs and AI workshop, make sure to have a laptop with you

events.name: Machine Learning Crash Course
events.description:
The course will start from the basics of Machine Learning to Real World Problem solutions. However, this crash course will be different from normal courses and learning environments as it will be focused in community based learning. There wont be a teacher or just students, here everyone will be a student and a teacher. We will work in pairs, teams and learn. There will be lots of sharing of ideas, concepts, programming skills and special sessions from experts in the field of machine learning.

This course is designed by Google itself. We will moderate the course as designed by Google but that doesn't limit us from coming up with different ways to run the course.

events.name: DevFest 2018
events.description:
DevFests are community-led, developer events hosted by GDG chapters around the globe focused on community building and learning about Google’s technologies. Each DevFest is inspired by and uniquely tailored to the needs of the developer community and region that hosts it.

Participants can attend the following options for the breakout sessions.
A. Speaker Session (30 min - 40 min)- Various Topics
- 30 minutes presentation/demo
- 5 minutes Q&A
- 5 minutes intermission between sessions
B. Hands-on Workshop ( 3 Hours each)
- Google Cloud Platform (GCP Essentials) Quiklabs Session
- Tensorflow Workshop

Register here: goo.gl/GbhwMp

events.name: Cloud Study Jam- Pokhara
events.description: In this quest, Participants will get hands-on practice with the Google Cloud Platform’s fundamental tools and services. GCP Essentials is Qwiklabs’ most popular quest and for good reason—you will come in with little, or no prior cloud knowledge and come out with practical experience that you can apply to any GCP project. From writing Cloud Shell commands and deploying your first virtual machine, to running applications on Kubernetes Engine with load balancing, GCP Essentials is a prime introduction to the platform’s features. 1-minute videos walk you through key concepts for each lab.
